ocational school \"Technik 2\" in Ludwigshafen. He was arrested shortly after. He was reportedly upset at the teacher for giving him low grades while he was a student at the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stern.de/panorama/bluttat-in-ludwigshafener-berufsschule-ex-schueler-stach-aus-wut-zu-1544645.html |title=Ex-Sch\u00fcler stach aus Wut zu |publisher=Stern.de |date=2010-02-18 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/Teacher+stabbed+death+over+marks/2584039/story.html|title=Teacher stabbed to death over 'bad marks'|accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref> Eight months later he was convicted of murder and sentenced to 14 years in prison and placement in a psychiatric facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/0,1518,724262,00.html |title=Gericht verurteilt Ex-Sch\u00fcler zu 14 Jahren Haft |publisher=Spiegel.de |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 23, 2010\n| [[Littleton, Colorado|Littleton]],<br>[[Colorado]],<br>United States\n| Bruco Strong Eagle Eastwood, 32\n|\n| 2 injured\n| A 32-year-old gunman, identified as Bruco Strong Eagle Eastwood, armed with a [[.30-06]] [[Winchester Model 70]] [[bolt-action rifle]], opened fire on students at [[Deer Creek Middle School]] at 3:30 pm (MST) as school was being let out in [[Littleton, Colorado]]. The gunman was later tackled by a math teacher and the teacher turned him into the police when they arrived on scene. The gunman shot and injured two students at the school before he was taken into custody. Eastwood was placed into a mental health facility for life.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/two-teens-injured-in-colorado-school-shooting/article1479363/ |title=Two teens injured in Colorado school shooting |publisher=Theglobeandmail.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100227030853/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/two-teens-injured-in-colorado-scho