and City, Tennessee]], United States\n| Jason Clinard, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 14-year-old Jason Clinard shot and killed school bus driver Joyce Gregory, who had been carrying a bus of approximately 24 students, Clinard is serving a life sentence in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.courttv.com/trials/taped/clinard/background_ctv.html?page=1 |title=Jason Clinard, 14 sentenced to life imprisonment for school bus driver killing |publisher=Courttv.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080202054719/http://www.courttv.com/trials/taped/clinard/background_ctv.html?page=1 |archivedate=2008-02-02 }}</ref>\n|-\n| March 21, 2005\n| [[Red Lake, Minnesota]], United States\n| [[Jeffrey Weise]], 16\n| 10 dead\n| 12+ injured\n| [[Red Lake shootings]]. Jeffrey Weise, a student at Red Lake High School in Red Lake, Minnesota, killed his grandfather and his grandfather's girlfriend before killing seven more people: five students, a teacher, and an unarmed security guard at Red Lake High School. The attack concluded when Weise exchanged fire with police, and then retreated to a classroom where he fatally shot himself.\n|-\n| June 10, 2005\n| [[Hikari, Yamaguchi]], Japan\n| ..., 18\n|\n| 58 injured\n| An 18-year-old student, whose name was not disclosed, threw a homemade bomb into a classroom at Hikari Senior High School, injuring 58 people, most of them slightly. The perpetrator later told police that the attack was directed against a group of students who had teased him for his shyness.<ref>[http://www.japantimes.co.jp/weekly/news/nn2005/nn20050618a1.htm Indiscriminate bomb targets student], ''[[The Japan Times]]'' (June 18, 2005)</ref>\n|-\n| September 9, 2005\n| [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| Jitrada Tantiwanichayasuk, 34\n|\n| 4 injured\n| Jitrada Tantiwanichayasuk, a mentally disturbed woman, stabbed four girls at Saint Joseph Convent School in Bangkok, before escaping on a motorcycle. She was later arrested and sentenced to four years 