ncock, 14\n|\n| 4 injured\n| 15-year-old Cameron Smith, and 14-year-old Cooper Caffrey, were shot when 14-year-old James Austin Hancock opened fire in the [[Madison High School (Middletown, Ohio)|Madison High School]] cafeteria with a .380 caliber handgun. 15-year-old Brant Murray, and 14-year-old Katherine Douchette, also suffered shrapnel injuries. Hancock originally brought the gun to campus to commit suicide, motivated by his upsetting home life. When he found that he did not have the courage to do so, he opened fire on Smith, his best friend, and then on other students. Hancock stated he began shooting at others to ensure that, no matter anything else that happened, \"... I wouldn't have to go back home\"<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.whio.com/news/news/crime-law/report-of-at-least-1-person-shot-at-madison-high-s/nqZq3/| title=Latest on Madison H.S. shooting|work=[[WHIO (AM)]] (Dayton, Ohio)| date=29 February 2016| author1=Rick McCrabb |author2=Lauren Pack |author3=Ed Richter}}</ref> Hancock was apprehended in a nearby wooded field.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.whio.com/news/news/crime-law/accused-madison-hs-shooter-in-court/nqbRN/| title=Parents of Madison H.S. shooting suspect speak; victim returns|work=[[WHIO (AM)]] (Dayton, Ohio)| date=2 March 2016| author=Lauren Clark}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 23, 2016}}\t\n| [[Antigo, Wisconsin]], United States\n| Jacob Wagner, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Two students at a prom at [[Antigo High School]] were shot and injured by 18-year-old former student Jakob Wagner. The students were randomly targeted. Wagner later exchanged fire with a school resource officer in the school's parking lot, and was captured after being shot and wounded by police. He died hours later in a hospital.\n|-\n|{{Dts|October 18, 2016}}\t\n| [[San Francisco, California]], United States\n| 4 suspects, 2 arrested for crime\n| \n| 4 injured\n| Four students were shot outside June Jordan High School for Equity, a San Francisco public high school